Housing market Photo:VCGChina's housing market showed signs of cooling down in November, data from a recent report showed.An index indicating the search for housing nationwide dropped 3 percent in November from one month earlier, according to a report jointly released by online marketplace 58.com and housing information platform anjuke.com.Specifically, the index for first-tier cities declined 2.4 percent from October, while that for second-tier cities decreased 2.9 percent, the report said.Third- and fourth-tier cities saw a 3.3-percent decline.The housing prices in 67 major cities averaged 16,420 yuan (2,506 U.S. dollars) per square meter last month, according to the report's online monitoring results. Year of the Rat stampSpectators dazzled at 131st Rose ParadeDiving Santa Global Times and Pakistan Observer signs MoUThe 3rd Sino-Nordic Cup Football Tournament draws crowdsGlobal Times begins cooperation with Sputnik